[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Generate Synthetic Patient Cohort
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The main recipe's Step 1 defines the cohort and Step 2 extracts features. Here we generate synthetic data that mimics what you'd get from a real EHR feature extraction pipeline. The synthetic data has four embedded subtypes with different clinical profiles, so we can verify the clustering recovers them.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def generate_synthetic_cohort(n_patients=2000, random_state=42):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Generate a synthetic heart failure cohort with embedded subtypes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This creates four distinct patient phenotypes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Metabolic HFpEF: high BMI, diabetes, preserved EF
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Ischemic progressive: low EF, prior MI, CAD history
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Elderly multimorbid: old, CKD, anemia, many comorbidities
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Young idiopathic: young, low EF, few comorbidities
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In real life, you'd never have these labels. That's the whole point of
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     unsupervised clustering. We include them here only so we can verify
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the algorithm recovers meaningful structure.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rng = np.random.default_rng(random_state)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Allocate patients to subtypes (unequal sizes, like reality)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     94[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     subtype_sizes = [600, 640, 400, 360]  # roughly 30%, 32%, 20%, 18%
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     assert sum(subtype_sizes) == n_patients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     records = []
